====Pokémon Adventures====
{{main|White (Adventures)}}
Hilda has a counterpart in [[Pokémon Adventures]] named White, who debuted in the {{MangaArc|Black & White}}. She works for an advertisement company called the [[BW Agency]], and she gets the idea to hire {{adv|Black}} upon seeing the bond the latter's {{p|Tepig}} had with a female of its species. In this [[canon]], she is the founder of the [[Pokémon Musical]] and [[Pokéstar Studios]].
